# Frontend React Stack Rule

For React/TypeScript frontend code:

- Prefer existing component and hook patterns already used in the codebase.
- Keep components focused and readable.
- Keep business logic out of presentational components where practical.
- Avoid deeply nested JSX when structure can be simplified.
- Prefer explicit props and readable state transitions.
- Reuse existing utilities and hooks before creating new ones.
- Do not introduce state abstractions or custom hooks unless they reduce real local complexity.
- Preserve existing UI behavior unless change is required.
- Keep type definitions readable and intention-revealing.
